29/03/2006
BEIJING, China -- Romanian President Traian Basescu announced on Tuesday (28 March) that the government is considering incentives for Chinese companies willing to invest in his country.
In a speech to a bilateral economic forum in Beijing, Basescu said that one proposed measure would simplify visa procedures for members of the Chinese business community.
Later in the day, he met with Chinese counterpart Hu Jintao, to discuss bilateral co-operation and foreign policy issues.
(Nine o'clock, People's Daily - 29/03/06;
Rompres - 28/03/06)
